Business Brief -- Safeway Inc.:
   Firm Has 4th-Quarter Loss;
   Same-Store Sales Fell 1.2%
Safeway said it took a charge of $71 million for
liabilities linked to the 1987 sale of its Houston division
to AppleTree Markets, which filed for bankruptcy last month.
The sale obligated Safeway to make payments on leases
assigned to AppleTree if the assignee was unable.
   Safeway took a charge of $11.4 million for debt retirement
in the quarter, ended Dec. 28. Excluding both charges, profit
was $34.7 million, or 35 cents a share.
   For all of 1991, net fell 37% to $54.9 million, or 48
cents a share, from $87.1 million, or 91 cents a share, in
1990. Excluding the charges, profit was $133.1 million, or
$1.16 a share. Revenue rose to $15.12 billion from $14.87
billion. Same-store sales were essentially flat.